

myWidget.geometry.set( { left : 0, width : 50 } );
  - means setting the geometry explicitly

myWidget.geometry.set( { left : 0, width : "50%" } );
  - percentage will be calculated according to parent's simple goemetry

myWidget.geometry.set( { left : 0, width : "auto" } );

  - width will be calculated to  fit all child widgets whoose geometry
    is set explicitly, which means  none of left, width, right, middle
    is defined as percentages